---

---

<section id="architecture" class="py-20">
  <div class="section-shell">
    <div class="mb-12 max-w-3xl">
      <div class="section-kicker mb-4">System model</div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-4 tracking-[-0.04em]">
        <span class="gradient-text">How It Works</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted max-w-2xl">
        From store entry to enabled skill in one managed flow.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-white/10 p-6 overflow-x-auto">
      <img src="/architecture.webp" alt="OntoSkills architecture" class="block mx-auto" style="max-height: 500px; width: auto; max-width: 100%;" />
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="border border-white/10 p-5">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-accent-cyan mb-2">Store Layer</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">The official store publishes compiled skills and metadata that the CLI can install remotely.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-white/10 p-5">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-accent-blue mb-2">Runtime Layer</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">OntoMCP loads enabled ontologies from the managed home directory and answers structured tool calls.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-white/10 p-5">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-accent-mint mb-2">Compiler Layer</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">OntoCore compiles custom SKILL.md sources when you need to author or extend the store locally.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
